To reproduce, start Eclipse and arrange your Workbench window so you have the 
Task view, Console view, Navigator view, and Outline view together in that 
order in a stack and nothing else open. I have them along the bottom of the 
Workbench window if it matters.

Make Tasks the current view. Exit Eclipse and restart it. Tasks should still 
be the current view. Select the Console view. Console is now the current view 
and its content area is all grayed out. Select Navigator. The Navigator view 
flashes up momentarily, then is replaced by the Console view, which is now all 
white except for the title area which says "CVS". If you select Navigator 
again, it sticks this time.

Forgot to mention - there has been nothing in the .log the last 10 times I 
reproduced this but the first couple of times I noticed these 2 errors that 
may or may not be related. After I got these I did a Reset Perspective and 
rearranged my views again, restarted a few times, and haven't seen the .log 
messages since then (though I still get the flip to Console described above).

Moving to Debug for the first problem since it is most likely due to the console
activating itself.

For the NPEs in setFocus and dispose, these look like a dup of bug 61545.
Were you running I20040514-0800 when you saw these too?
If so, any clues to reproducing this would be most helpful.  Please annotate bug
61545.

Moving to CVS. I think this is due to the fact that activating the navigator 
caues CVS activity (refereshing label decorations?). This likle starts up the 
CVS console if you have the preference on. This may "show" the console. 
However, it might be a bug on the part of CVS - i.e. showing the console, 
rather than "adding" the console?

When the user selects to show the CVS console in the preferences we show it. On
startup we simply add the cvs console if the preference is set.

I can't duplicate this with the latest I-build. I've tried a couple of different
scenarios (e.g. using breakpoints in show console code) and can't see how
activating the cvs plug-in is causing the console view to show.
